						               													<description>The game takes place in the medieval Europe where the players lead their estates as landlords. They must hurry with afforestation, regulation of rivers, and cultivating the fields to build a nicer and richer manor.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player rolls his 6 dice, then chooses one of them and draws the area corresponding to his number/colour on the map, then passes the other dice to the left neighbour using the dice holder and chooses one of the 5 dice he has, then passes this one and so on. When you run out of dice, the round is over and the next round begins in the same way. The game ends when all players have completed their map, i.e. filled in all the squares.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player who scores the most points from building ponds, plough, forest, river, house wins. Each area has a different scoring system.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 2 variants of the game, one is a more tactical while the other one is faster. During the game common and hidden goal cards can be used optionally.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
